column2: Sunny- breezy- 85 F- some algal blooms.
Sunny- 75 F- slight breeze- lilies along shore- a few weeds at boat landing.
Cool- 48 degrees- cloudy with occasional drizzle
Sunny- warm- partly cloudy- slight NE breeze- high water levels.  Water clarity unusually low.  Secchi readings are typically 10-15.  Must have hit the turnover
Lake choppy.  Southwest wind 8-10 mph.  Cold front activity beginning to develop.  Great conditions. . . normal for Jordan although secchi readings for '94 are shallower than '93 season.
Overcast- warm- thunderstorm earlier in the morning.
Sunny- slight breeze- beautiful day- 45 degrees.
4" of rain in one day in the previous week- drizzly and overcast.  Lake level: very high
Partly cloudy. 2-5 mph W wind. 78 deg F. Sunny as of 1:45 pm.
Mostly sunny- blue skies. 5 mph W wind. 90 deg F. Skiers- motorboats- jet skis present.
Sunny- high cirrus clouds. 78 deg F. 5-10 mph WSW wind. Wind blew boat. Not sure of actual depths as van dorn bottle was not perpendicular.
Sunny- hazy- humid. Sun through the cloud cover. 85 deg F. W wind 10-15 mph. 11 am- wind was about 20 mph.
Foggy- humid. 65 deg F. 5 mph NE wind.
Sunny- clear skies. 68 deg F. 10 mph E wind. Lots of tiny- spherical algae present in water.
No sun with light winds.  Lot of tree bloom on the lake surface.  Lake level is up since Fall of 2008 but unable to determine how much.
Full sun and light breeze.  Lake level at 0" after being down to -1.5"

column1: A Boat Census was taken on 8/21/12.
